  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project has 3 specific objectives: 1. 20 Community-Supported Wing Schools enrol 2000 out of reach school age children (50% girls) 2. 160 Wing School and untrained teachers (of whom 25% are women) have improved their professional development and apply mother tongue instruction, gender-sensitive and learner-centred approaches 3. The capacity of 40 School Management Committees and local and national civil society organizations are strengthened, contributing to transparent and accountable school governance and, influencing national education policy.</narrative>
